Package <Unnamed>

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    arrayOP
    The arrayOP class does operations on arrays of integers.
    CH
    This CH class implements the recursive formula of Caporaso-Harris in "Counting plane curves of any genus" for computing the number of nodal curves on the projective plane.
    F0table
    The F0table class uses dynamic programming approach to implement the recursive formula of Vakil in "Counting curves on rational surfaces" to compute the number of singular curves on P^1*P^1 which satisfy tangency conditions with a given line in |O(1,0)|.
    HirTable
    This HirTable class uses dynamic programming approach to implement the recursive formula of Vakil in "Counting curves on rational surfaces" to compute the number of singular curves on Hirzebruch surfaces F_n which satisfy tangency conditions with the divisor E = h-nf.
    Key
    The Key class has three static methods to concatenate intputs into an ArrayList of Integer.

    partitions
    The partitions class generates all partitions of length less or equal to maxLength of positive integers less or equal to n.
    seqOP
    The seqOP class does operations on ArrayLists of integers.
